messages.subject: Awards Ceremony is this Saturday, July 26th - World’s Largest Hackathon presented by Bolt
messages.body:
( http://devpost.com )

( https://worldslargesthackathon.devpost.com/ )

The Finale is here!  Join us Saturday, July 26th for the World’s Largest Hackathon Awards Ceremony, a 90-minute virtual celebration open to everyone.

We’re giving away $1M in prizes! We’ll be announcing over 60 prizes live and recognizing the incredible projects this global community built during the hackathon. Expect guest speakers, judge highlights, and moments that showcase the power of creativity of this community!

 Date: Saturday, July 26th
 Time: 10am PT / 1pm ET
 Location: YouTube Livestream
Link ( https://bolt.fyi/awards-ceremony )
 RSVP or Add to Calendar: Event page ( https://app.getriver.io/beta/events/worlds-largest-hackathon-award-ceremony-cxnk ) 

Can’t make it live? No worries, the ceremony will be recorded and available to watch afterward. Come celebrate with us and see what the World’s Largest Hackathon has created. 

We'll see you soon!

You received this email because you signed up for World’s Largest Hackathon presented by Bolt. If you're no longer participating, you can unregister here ( https://worldslargesthackathon.devpost.com/ ).

messages.subject: Your Bi-Weekly Roundup: New AI Challenges & Big Winner Announcements
messages.body:
Hey builders,

This week’s roundup is all about pushing boundaries with AI. Explore new challenges, see how developers are building real-world impact with agentic AI, and don't forget to check out the winning projects from the AI in Action Hackathon and Perplexity Hackathon—they’re seriously impressive.

Let’s dive in 👇

 

*******************
FEATURED HACKATHONS
*******************

( https://tidb-2025-hackathon.devpost.com//?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=24072025 )TiDB AgentX Hackathon 2025 ( https://tidb-2025-hackathon.devpost.com//?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=24072025 )

By: PingCAP

Forge Agentic AI for Real-World Impact

🏆 $30K+ in prizes 
🗓️ Submissions Aug 1-Sep 15

Register for the hackathon here ( https://tidb-2025-hackathon.devpost.com//?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=24072025 )( https://tableau.devpost.com///?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=24072025 )Tableau Next Virtual Hackathon ( https://tableau.devpost.com///?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=24072025 )

By: Tableau

Lead the Agentic Analytics Era and Win Big Prizes

🏆 $45K in prizes 
🗓️ Submissions Sep 18

Register for the hackathon here ( https://tableau.devpost.com///?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=24072025 )( https://kiro.devpost.com//?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=24072025 )Proof of Concept ( https://proofofconcept.devpost.com//?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=24072025 )

By: XION

If you could prove any data on the internet - what would you build?

🏆 $25K in prizes 
🗓️ Sep 19 deadline

Register for the hackathon here ( https://proofofconcept.devpost.com//?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=24072025 ) 

*************************
OTHER TRENDING HACKATHONS
*************************

* Google Maps Platform Awards: ( https://googlemapsplatformawards.devpost.com//?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=24072025 ) Special prizes, Jul 31 deadline
*
Africa Deep Tech Challenge 2025: ( https://adtc-2025.devpost.com//?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=24072025 ) $20K in prizes, Jul 31 deadline
* Qloo LLM Hackathon: ( https://qloo-hackathon.devpost.com//?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=24072025 ) $25K in prizes, Aug 1 deadline
* Revenuecat Shipaton 2025: ( https://revenuecat-shipaton-2025.devpost.com//?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=24072025 ) $274K in prizes, Sep 30 deadline
Explore more hackathons ( https://devpost.com/hackathons//?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter )  

***************************
RECENT WINNER ANNOUNCEMENTS
***************************

 

************************************************************************************
AI in Action Winners Announced! ( https://ai-in-action.devpost.com/project-gallery )
************************************************************************************

messages.subject: Competition Launch: Jigsaw - Agile Community Rules Classification
messages.body:
Kaggle








Hi Nouman Usman,

Every subreddit has its own rules, which makes moderation a tricky task. In  
this competition, you'll build models that predict whether a Reddit comment  
broke a rule, based on real data and rule types inspired by actual  
subreddit guidelines.

You're challenged to create a binary classifier that can handle the quirks  
of different communities. As more data is released over time, you'll need  
to stay nimble and adapt your approach.





Total Prizes:

$100,000


Entry Deadline:

October 22, 2025




Learn More



Your work could contribute to smarter, more adaptive moderation tools  
across online platforms.

Good luck,

Walter Reade
Kaggle Data Scientist



Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043

messages.subject: Kaggle Benchmarks: Introducing Community-Driven Evaluation
messages.body:
Kaggle








Hi Nouman Usman,

At Kaggle, we believe in the power of community-driven evaluation. That's  
why we're thrilled to introduce Kaggle Benchmarks, our new platform making  
it easier for anyone to test and understand model capabilities.

To showcase the platform, we are unveiling the ICML 2025 AI Experts  
Benchmark crowdsourced at the ICML conference in Vancouver. We evaluated  
over 30 tasks that reflect the real-world interests of AI researchers and  
industry experts on leading models, including Gemini 2.5 Pro, Claude 4  
Sonnet, o4 mini, and DeepSeek-R1.


Kaggle Benchmarks Platform with metrics, leaderboards, and customization  
options



Want to create your own evals to test models at no cost or infrastructure  
setup? Join the waitlist for early access to custom task creation! Plus,  
check out kaggle.com/benchmarks featuring 70+ leaderboards like SciCode,  
GPQA, and Meta's new MultiLoKo benchmark.





Read the full announcement



Join us in building the future of AI evaluation!

Happy Kaggling!
The Kaggle Team

messages.subject: Competition Launch: MAP - Charting Student Math Misunderstandings
messages.body:
Kaggle








Hi Nouman Usman,

Students are often asked to explain their mathematical reasoning. These  
explanations provide insights into student thinking, and often reveal  
underlying misconceptions.

Tagging students' explanations as 'containing potential misconceptions' is  
valuable for diagnostics, but it is time-consuming and challenging to scale.

In this competition, you'll build NLP models that predict potential math  
misconceptions in student explanations, enabling teachers to catch common  
errors faster.





Total Prizes:

$55,000


Entry Deadline:

October 8, 2025




Learn More



Your work could help improve math instruction and make it easier for  
teachers to identify and address students' incorrect thinking.

Good luck,

Walter Reade
Kaggle Data Scientist



Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043

messages.subject: New Hackathons, Big Wins, and More
messages.body:
Hey builders,

Welcome to this edition of the Devpost roundup!

Check out the latest hackathons to join, see which ones are trending, get inspired by recent winners, and discover what’s new in the community.

Let’s go →

 

*******************
FEATURED HACKATHONS
*******************

( https://qloo-hackathon.devpost.com//?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=10072025 )Qloo LLM Hackathon ( https://qloo-hackathon.devpost.com//?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=10072025 )

By: Qloo

Join Qloo’s first global hackathon, a month-long event inviting developers, builders, and creatives to explore what’s possible at the intersection of LLMs and Qloo’s API.

🏆 $25K in prizes 
🗓️ Aug 1 deadline

Register for the hackathon here ( https://qloo-hackathon.devpost.com//?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=10072025 )( https://revenuecat-shipaton-2025.devpost.com//?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=10072025 )Revenuecat Shipaton 2025 ( https://revenuecat-shipaton-2025.devpost.com//?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=10072025 )

By: RevenueCat

Ship apps and start making money.

🏆 $274K in prizes 
🗓️ Submissions Aug 1-Sep 30

Register for the hackathon here ( https://revenuecat-shipaton-2025.devpost.com//?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=10072025 ) 

*************************
OTHER TRENDING HACKATHONS
*************************

* Adobe Express Add-ons Hackathon: ( https://adobeexpress.devpost.com//?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=10072025 ) $30K in prizes, Jul 21 deadline
*
RevenueCat's World Paywall Speed Building Championships 2025: ( https://revenuecatpaywallsworldchamps.devpost.com//?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=10072025 ) $5K in prizes, Jul 21 deadline
*
Google Maps Platform Awards: ( https://googlemapsplatformawards.devpost.com//?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=10072025 ) Special prizes, Jul 31 deadline
* Africa Deep Tech Challenge 2025: ( https://adtc-2025.devpost.com//?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=10072025 ) $20K in prizes, Jul 31 deadline
* Proof of Concept ( https://proofofconcept.devpost.com//?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter&utm_campaign=10072025 ): $25K in prizes, Sep 12 deadline
Explore more hackathons ( https://devpost.com/hackathons//?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter )  

***************************
RECENT WINNER ANNOUNCEMENTS
***************************

 ( https://hpaistudio.devpost.com/project-gallery )
 

****************************************************************************************************
HP& NVIDIA Developer Challenge Winners Announced! ( https://hpaistudio.devpost.com/project-gallery )
****************************************************************************************************

We’re thrilled to announce the winners of the HP & NVIDIA Developer Challenge! From real-time emotion insights to document forensics and immersive 3D scenes, these projects showcased the power of HP AI Studio and the creativity of our developer community. See winning projects > ( https://hpaistudio.devpost.com/project-gallery )

 

 

**********************
📣 DEVPOST IS HIRING
**********************

 
Our Project Management and Marketing teams are hiring! Here's your chance to work behind the scenes on some of the world’s most exciting software competitions—and get a front-row seat to how today’s cutting-edge tech gets built.

Apply Now! ( https://jsco.re/gh7n0 ) Join our Discord ( https://discord.com/invite/mYGykt3Dnx?utm_source=devpost&utm_medium=newsletter ) to learn more about our hackathons, find teammates, and more!

messages.subject: CPC benchmark preview: First look at quarterly results
messages.body:
Hi Nouman,

As you launch ad campaigns for the second half of the year, how
confident are you that those dollars are driving the right

messages.subject: Understanding your Manus credits
messages.body:
Empathizing with customer pain point, explaining how the credit system works, 
empowering the customer to start building with credits 


 <https://manus.im/app> 


Hi there,

Welcome back! You might be wondering how Manus credits work, if you have 
enough, or what happens if they run out. Don't worry; we’ll cover everything 
you need so you can start building with complete confidence and control.

  



What are Manus credits?


Like many AI tools, Manus uses credits for your Agent to complete tasks. Every 
time your Agent performs a task — whether that’s creating slides, generating 
videos, or deploying apps — it consumes a certain amount of credits. If a task 
fails, any credits used will be fully refunded to your account.

  



How many credits does a task use?


The number of credits needed varies by task complexity and completion time. To 
check your current credit balance and usage history, simply hover above your 
name at the bottom left corner of your dashboard, and click “credits”.

  


  



Build with confidence


Every day, you automatically receive 300 free credits, so you always have a 
base to work with.

Looking for additional credits? Refer a friend (or several!) and receive 500 
additional credits for each.Click here 
<https://manus.im/app?openInvitationList=1> to share your personal link to 
friends!

Ready to tackle bigger and more powerful tasks? Check out 
<https://manus.im/home#pricing> our different membership tiers to see which 
plan best suits your needs.

  

Start building  <https://manus.go.link/fGlf6> 

Explore different plans  <https://manus.im/home#pricing> 
  

Happy creating,

The Manus Team

Creating stunning presentations has never been easier. Simply tell Manus what 
you need—"Help me create a slide about sustainable energy"—and watch as Manus

messages.subject: Exciting news: your Bolt tokens now roll over!
messages.body:
Now your tokens stay with you, even if you don’t use them right away 🎊

Hello builders and happy Tuesday! We have some super exciting items to share today:

YOUR TOKENS NOW ROLLOVER!!

You asked, we shipped. Moving forward, all of your unused Bolt tokens will now roll over to the next month!

↪️ No more lost tokens

🏃 Build at your own pace

📦 Save ‘em up for big launches

We hope this change gives you less stress and more focus on what works for you. Learn more here (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/VVRYX94hX7vcW4d1wcm6TXQrBW11fj5c5yMbL7N3tskFg3lcq-W7lCdLW6lZ3mzW2C_RmF7CGVFkW439F5p58wq6zW4bxB3180fY4HW48c4zN7SNs-gW6JPcsG78r47zW6LHfnq6qMNWRW7t0JSd840VXNN8H0hK5mvBrpW5p6fXS4KHDGwW9cmJjG8QB15MW5J7GnF85Skb9W25KNxR2mrY_RW7qVJ753cB10LV100JN3TvjcfW5TfJgB78S0zRW8ygH536xLVvkW2_T2hS5GP38ZW18l8Wq7QQnlkW7cZRLB5Y1M_HW2RJ4l-8MCNLPW5MGYVk9c4tzVW5QxFn31F7-99W6z7nk97Tw-fCW7y6MF48XMBcSf8LWXZP04 ) .

Tune in or say hello this week 👋

Join us today and tomorrow for 2 extra special livestreams:

Today at 9AM PT:

Reddit for Builders: Find Your People, Grow Your Project (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/VVRYX94hX7vcW4d1wcm6TXQrBW11fj5c5yMbL7N3tskG83lcq-W95jsWP6lZ3mBW2V8PP92GMZr_W1BFrN_1mx3htW9llH3p5vxcrCVz7zr56d66yXW4cM-gF8XzCxVW5CLpLY5Vwby-W4LgngY1Ndl-PW8WJnSx8qslQNW4QqQL95fZm4cW186s2N2w3D4JW57hHXK6CGFrkW1yw2kZ8WQ-DsW18wTNY6gYSb1W5MKqmT30dDhxW1d-9BS7q-6LWW5jX3N73GxJDyVCwND18MxRkZW7GG-JZ3hJTPlN10g4032Qt_pVKPWln3L9gRqW3Xmw597f0KmQW5v4-yD5NPk5PW11ZRXb7_tmwjW4cd0_f32md6pW3v3LHy6cNX4mVDKDbb6_Dv4yV3vJsP1JrNvBW6CYc1p3XhbxfN7ssCP744TXsW7KDrN25P58b-f8llLZY04 )

We’re going live in a just a bit with Reddit, Inc. to break down how you can reach users, get featured, and monetize your projects! Don’t miss this chance to learn how to make the most of the homepage of the internet.

Wednesday at 9AM PT:

GV x Bolt: Building Bold Ideas (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/VVRYX94hX7vcW4d1wcm6TXQrBW11fj5c5yMbL7N3tskFz3lcq-W7Y8-PT6lZ3lXW7G-7bB7ZH5_kW59t2Kp2D2PVqW2_lzKv2YTD2bW3Hp3WR2Q7NkQW3WKcD_5d4nYyW427Qn02k9V-RN7WWgdZTmrSqVG8lfn8P0yKJW35RC7_6_wSWRW1yFYkp2DzV0lW7kM0DJ3hT-c7W3sn3yf6JkbzXN89J7kDFdPT3W6KctwM51MLlSW5YGkk45NQRCyVbYhqy2crHdBW4nF1xG28DwycW222z-33mP2VrW3Cq4Lk89pTG9W3T5VFk5K0Y9-W8MKscw6t_fqyW7gtS6Q5pknQdN75yff66cNg3W8QJ8kF1rvWN3W3znXsG8whVzSW2wMr9D4f8YZwf12cvns04 )

Join us for a conversation between general partner at GV, Erik Nordlander and Bolt Co-Founder, Eric Simons. They’ll explore topics you might find interesting, like the early days of StackBlitz, the search for product-market fit, and what it takes to build a business in today’s landscape.

Curious about getting on the App Store?

Check out this blog (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/VVRYX94hX7vcW4d1wcm6TXQrBW11fj5c5yMbL7N3tskFz3lcq-W7Y8-PT6lZ3nxW204KBM401BJWW7C436R6Mm1S6W8Xy3587lFKjsW867hTp2HYwG6V-D_Jq7wFsbYW2RplDt7tz5YTW46Y25p8Cc865N5-R0qXD17NDW1b_J0D7P3Xp5W78WRy51lcjb-W3bllpR3M5L53W1g2fnC14Y1vzW3J-7mC8dr7B_VGmgZm2wM0wVW5D9wL_6ZMpYQVNThr350kWgGW6snmHs8DjPzkW4cZgjX3bFscPW3Clb9f3zlvCZW8mRSdv3DP2SBW1X1L401pfB3bW4g700G11RkG6W8SKQyb55qkTSW4fPmRP2q3bsRM9sZXsjq8brW1-BbKJ5hnhWJf1RFpXK04 ) detailing how one builder used Bolt and Expo to go from prompt all the way to the App Store (real payments and all) in just two weeks.

World's Largest Hackathon Writing Challenge

From now until July 31, this challenge (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/VVRYX94hX7vcW4d1wcm6TXQrBW11fj5c5yMbL7N3tskD45jMY8W50kH_H6lZ3lLW7ZyXgv2lF7wGMZKGzqv1SWYW6CZjvv7RY8myMVlbx1b-6DmVldw_n5rX6LCW299XBV942zc0W4pGJbh5j9F5nW8bBx7K1QlVY_W36WX-D7XqC1FW2kgPwZ5kLghSW3CNL2d7GSXT0Mg7jWn3Tv8jW5jFmh_2PMBYkW1pwrSw84q2XQW6rq-Hw2RmdssW64gl-24zfxhMVvwbv63nZh6jW7Mf_YF75c8THW1Nvdqw2jGc2qW5tLQ3v3qQ-zqW1LK1hH5ShgjLW7dBNlR15422JW63Xqn42ztx2QW1DnGJS2xqZBmVm4v2J7BjyYdW52KtBT330tfvW68fYCJ1X_qG1W8pCTnP5v3zjJVsSxy45L-97LW2sSkfs8_Gn5TW6W_qwS9kGLLfVXzBvj8dZGzlf3-Gd7T04 ) offers everyone a chance to document and share their building experience. There will be at least one winner per prompt, and each winner will receive an exclusive DEV badge (plus, all valid submissions will earn a completion badge). Choose to enter using 1 of the 3 prompts:

- Building with Bolt: Share your project development experience and technical journey: what you built with Bolt, any challenges you tackled, favorite code snippets or prompts, or how AI-powered dev changed your approach.
- Beyond the Code: Tell us about the human side of your hackathon experience: team collaboration dynamics, IRL events, connections, mentors, community moments, networking experiences, or shout-outs to people who made your hackathon memorable.
- After the Hack: Share what's next for you and your project, and reflect on what you learned, whether you're continuing development, launching a startup, or found that building became more important than competing.

Enjoy those tokens rolling over!

Eric Simons

CEO & Co-Founder, Bolt.new (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/VVRYX94hX7vcW4d1wcm6TXQrBW11fj5c5yMbL7N3tskDH3lcq-W69sMD-6lZ3nYW4BtNGP1fXJVwW2Pm_zg6DWS8-VnX4Rx6JpzLgW8FHy3r4gQL8zVt4H6j8sZD9vW3n5LSL3TxZ9zW3MzTh58-dkF3W8Q7YC-6L35JrW86bw3G63kf31N70BmHxD7wPgW6MWjB_4vHTXwW2Jb2kY2dYv8LW1N66MP1Qp4GdVP9bZg7K57RcW74KwhF8rKzcDN3fJFs0vzNMLW85nKxL4Ddg_0W3n74tR7rqSgkW9m3XV_4swrq1W8XHX4w20SN1Lf8MJLNK04 )

messages.subject: Your Manus Journey Begins Now
messages.body:
Hello, 

Welcome to Manus. 

Most AI tools are like that colleague who's great at brainstorming but never 
follows through. They can chat, they can suggest, but when it comes to get work 
done? You're on your own.

Manus is different. Think of it as an AI tool that finally executes your ideas 
and delivers concrete results.

  


  



How Manus delivers


Manus has its own computer where it operates various tools - programming, data 
analysis, design software, and more - to deliverables ready to be used. Whether 
it's creating files, building websites, generating images and videos, or 
developing applications, Manus uses its toolkit to turn ideas into reality.

  



Your reliable colleague that work synchronously with you


Start a stock analysis before your flight departure and receive the complete 
report when you touch down. Conduct research before a meeting and get

Welcome to FASHN

 
Hi Nouman 👋
We’re thrilled to have you join our community 🎉
 



Where to start?
 
Discover a range of tools in our app, including virtual try-on, mockups, a background changer, and more!

How to generate fashion photoshoots?
To start generating fashion photoshoots from our studio [https://app.fashn.ai/studio],

Not ready to commit?

Thank you for joining us on this exciting journey.

- Aya & Dan, FASHN Co-Founders 💛

messages.subject: Get 100 free minutes from Sonix 🤩
messages.body:
Hi Nouman, 
 If you haven't seen our referral program yet, I'd like to tell you about it. You can get unlimited free minutes for referring your friends. 
 Here’s how it works. It’s super simple: 
 Step 1 Get your unique referral link here: https://my.sonix.ai/refer 
 Step 2 Copy, email, or share your unique referral link with your friends 
 Step 3 When they subscribe to a Premium or Enterprise plan, you get 100 free minutes and they get 100 free minutes That's it! Thanks in advance for sharing Sonix with your friends. :) 
 Richard Tampus Customer Success Manager

messages.subject: Post-hackathon blues? We've got you
messages.body:
Thank you to all of our hackathon participants

We've partnered with Netlify (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/VX4Xxb8rXFJMW7ND-8N3_HmbhW1n-N735ywxlZMfRfkn3lcq-W69sMD-6lZ3ndW6vJd2s6tyKmKW189h8D47p29FN3pWLXZy1GqWW1WMKR53W3-8jVJjQbT1HYr1JW8sr48g1YrqMHVp0n5z1kZL0-W1ysxbs4FtQTZW64614v1zQK4fW3C3qwH7znprjW1f16yf8cMGdZW5V1vzD3KjV5DW45pfFX7BNFTzW20MvTw90f7L7W4-sDfl7y_mslW9jGWpD76Xf5cW5j7Zbm2JlkngN1Nmq-bpQlsPW5nsWhM8X0Zp0W7rTRvt2yRM3Hf5gq42-04 ) to bring you this email of exciting news and updates!

What an incredible month it has been! Seeing you all show up, dive in, and share your inspiring stories throughout the hackathon has been truly amazing. This community is the heart of everything we do, and your participation made it unforgettable. Thank you from the bottom of our hearts ❤️

What's next?

Our panel of judges will be diving into all your incredible projects in preparation for the upcoming award ceremony on July 26. Be sure to save the date! And we will be sharing more details around the award ceremony soon!

Can’t wait? Neither can we honestly. So in the meantime, join us and the Bolt community on Twitter (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/VX4Xxb8rXFJMW7ND-8N3_HmbhW1n-N735ywxlZMfRfkH3lcq-W6N1vHY6lZ3nQW18M5gr4fS4KqN16fpwtbHTBTN5cX7_VkVGy_W8WlVrf7ZVGRGVrmBYw7_DxTQW4Fkk_d5skQ4zW23gyM621DkpBW3HJ5xv2sjcVHW1W-9Q97WbcXlW41Pw8j1MKpJJMrD7q7Gv6zKW23WfYv7rLxBBVt8sT54dVRMVW1ZRwpk6P_1GnW8qBmGn3tVMgrW7-r-3H7fpPLVVtV3MB6X8kndW8x8JnJ6MRCHcW3lKjl23Yj-JkW8Nwq981PfM4kV_8m8M4nn_g2W1HYXh96Y4CT_f4K_9dx04 ) , Discord (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/VX4Xxb8rXFJMW7ND-8N3_HmbhW1n-N735ywxlZMfRfkn3lcq-W69sMD-6lZ3lmW2fsXQr4c_LMSMTvhHPcWsBRW8r0Q7825Pm4cW6jnQKh1T8MnLVKTNGp4LGMkWW1mxL398bzr1SW3b2Y1D8Nm-XlW44F_Wy77SkJ3W5vzq5N5cX7bZW7lnzX_2j8x7hW17N4XN7ZKB4FW7ZdcDZ5zS6zHW3PBWfy94bspbW2fd_RN1ZXnzwW2T6TQ58WXc8xW5Qy2MZ8lVFNRVR23Fr4zc09yW7WnshM6-_yXQW4K7g6r6yxHxxN5QYJd99__5lf2YgHf204 ) , and Reddit (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/VX4Xxb8rXFJMW7ND-8N3_HmbhW1n-N735ywxlZMfRfkH3lcq-W6N1vHY6lZ3mbW3l3tQN6b8BDCW5Y_nlC98jf0yW4c0HQc17V74WW4pwcF7858nlLW1Q_7RH5JGfL_W6gdPvm1hX9GbW8c5ddP8CnL7qN5xLF-2RL2NkW6r7TzD4VSfx1W72HcmZ1FKTZkW81btj_2gC1L2N8JFHHDjjTVHW5yNCDX8c4wJFW8DL9Rx4KP65pW680fnb3m9qmtW4rHNmj4GRWThW2VCRvR4YWHkVVmm3m51fbgJXW1chLzF3js918N6HZphZ-gwMPW6tPkkq32YLr8W112TKQ12xzrff6R5CrT04 ) .

Join us in NYC

Are you in the NYC area? We will be teaming up with the folks at Framer to host Design Space NYC — an invite-only creative coworking experience for founders, designers, and product builders for a day of focused work, real-time feedback, and new connections.

Whether you're building a new site, polishing UX, or need a fresh perspective…this is your space to make real progress. Space is limited, so request to join (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/VX4Xxb8rXFJMW7ND-8N3_HmbhW1n-N735ywxlZMfRfkH3lcq-W6N1vHY6lZ3mhN4mJttL3XXWcW3cp0ND7hF3cpW8_14qj555FjwV42RlF4dnQ9GW1WCcpZ73ddDyW5ncY0C8rDKgyMz2HsdHNT6-W1hn8mT7B9vKvW8M0SHr4T-jrzW3w2Rdv40lj8LW7P4h3t8nF-HrW13h-BV8JsC5VW1yQPCP2T-8yjW4RCBG78Q5gHrW8Lzzh81hPNXqW3MVmqQ2zq5f4V-Jz6F49XHCSN7QHkN4F-VG-W5QNh4J8jwPpMN54q-Fyl-G2PVr4cMm5vvnrDW2PSgKl231Qtcf6GZKJF04 ) today 👀

Bolt Gallery is live

Bolt Gallery is officially live! This is our showcase of standout projects built with Bolt. It's a place to get featured and a resource for the community to see what's possible! messages.subject: Top 5 things you should know about Sonix 🚀
messages.body:
Hi Nouman, 
 By now you’ve hopefully discovered some magical features inside Sonix besides speedy transcription. I wanted to highlight 5 more: 
 ​1/ Search - get instant access to valuable insights across all your transcripts ​2/ AI analysis - aggregate themes and trends by analyzing data across multiple transcripts ​3/ Automated translation - help teams collaborate more effectively in multinational settings ​4/ Automated subtitles - streamline content creation, enhance accessibility, and improve audience engagement ​5/ Custom dictionary - Ensure consistent recognition and spelling of industry-specific terms, jargon, or brand names. ​ We offer other industry-specific features and language models tailored to your needs—just reach out, and we’ll assist you. 
 Richard Tampus Customer Success Manager

messages.subject: This is IT! - World’s Largest Hackathon presented by Bolt
messages.body:
( http://devpost.com )

( https://worldslargesthackathon.devpost.com/ )

This is IT! Deadline Day Has Arrived! Today, Monday, June 30th, 2025, is the final countdown for the World's Largest Hackathon presented by Bolt. Time is of the essence! All submissions must be finalized and submitted by 2:00 pm PT sharp to be considered for the groundbreaking prizes and global recognition. This is your last chance to make history and showcase your innovative project built with Bolt.new. Don't miss this pivotal moment to join the record books!

Here is a complete video walkthrough of How to Submitting Your Project ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SylgkOajqrY )

( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SylgkOajqrY )

 

Frequently Asked Questions
--------------------------

How do I share the credentials for judges to test my project?
Please try to ensure the judges don't need special access privileges for your project. If absolutely necessary, try to pre-fill it within the URL you submit on the Additional Info tab.

My account got flagged by Devpost’s automated system! What should I do?
Do not panic! Please email support@devpost.com and let them know “My account was suspended by accident, please help by removing the suspension. Thank you.” They will resolve it with you within a few hours. If this impedes your ability to finish your submission please inform them of that as well.  

How do I select the Bonus Prizes and Challenge Prizes I want to enter into?
There are 8 Challenges and 12 Bonus Awards. Those complete lists can be found here: https://worldslargesthackathon.devpost.com/details/prizes
When submitting your project, please note that only 4 Bonus Prizes are available on the submission form as all of the other bonus prizes (like “Most Viral Project” and “Creative Use of AI”) are to be selected by the judges. The 4 available on the submission form require participants to opt into and provide information to be eligible.
If submitting to a Challenge prizes, please note that some require additional information. See the below checklist for details. 

 

Project Eligibility Checklist

* Are you creating a NEW application primarily built with Bolt.new?
* Have you added the Built with Bolt badge to the publicly deployed version (see guidance here ( https://worldslargesthackathon.devpost.com/details/badgeguidelines ))?
* Have you recorded a project demo video? Is your video uploaded to YouTube and public? Is it coherent and shows your app working? Remember that any content over three minutes will not be viewed by judges.
* Did you submit the project on Devpost here ( https://devpost.com/submit-to/24786-world-s-largest-hackathon-presented-by-bolt/manage/submissions?_gl=1*ouxgv8*_gcl_au*NTY2NTgwMjYuMTc0ODg4OTI3Nw..*_ga*MTU3ODM4MjUwOC4xNzQ4ODg5Mjc3*_ga_0YHJK3Y10M*czE3NTA0MjQyODUkbzczJGcxJHQxNzUwNDMwODk2JGo2MCRsMCRoMA.. )?  Your project should show as SUBMITTED and to be eligible it must include:
* A URL to a publicly available version of a project that meets all the requirements and is fully functional
* The Bolt.new project URL (must start with https://bolt.new/~/… ( https://bolt.new/~/%E2%80%A6 ))
* A text description that should explain the features and functionality of your Project and also explain how it meets any Challenge Requirements or Bonus prize.
* Selection of your geographical region and all Challenge and Bonus prizes and proof of eligibility to those. Only a few of the Challenges and Bonus prizes require something, but don't miss out on them:
* Make More Money Challenge requires a RevenueCat project ID.
* Voice AI Challenge requires an ElevenLabs account email address.
* Deploy Challenge requires a Netlify Team account's slug.
* Startup Challenge requires a Supabase Organization Slug.
* Blockchain Challenge requires a Algorand block explorer link to data related to project.
* Silly Sh!t Challenge requires a Reddit username and link to Reddit demo post.
* Custom Domain Challenge requires nothing extra!
* Conversational AI Video Challenge requires nothing extra!
* All of your teammates added as teammates. Remind them to accept the invitation so that they’re listed on the project!

Go for the Gold! (And Global Recognition!)

 

You received this email because you signed up for World’s Largest Hackathon presented by Bolt. If you're no longer participating, you can unregister here ( https://worldslargesthackathon.devpost.com/ ).

messages.subject: Demo Video Tips - World’s Largest Hackathon presented by Bolt
messages.body:
( http://devpost.com )

( https://worldslargesthackathon.devpost.com/ )

Three days remain to submit your project in the World's Largest Hackathon! Submissions close June 30th at 2pm PT.

Your submission video isn't just a showcase—it's your shot at history! Often the first thing judges see, it's your chance to truly stand out.

Here’s how to make your three minutes legendary:

* Make Every Second Count: This isn’t just any video. It’s your highlight reel in a global competition!
* Craft Your Pitch: Hit the essentials! Project requirements? Tools used? Problem solved? Solution unveiled? Include them all!
* Demonstrate Brilliance: Show judges how your project shines in real-world scenarios.
* Time-Saving Tip: Write out a script and practice it! Precision is key.
* Pro Tip (Beware Procrastination!): Video uploads can take hours! Don’t let technical glitches dash your record-setting dreams.

Once you are all set, get started on your submission on Devpost here ( https://devpost.com/submit-to/24786-world-s-largest-hackathon-presented-by-bolt/manage/submissions?_gl=1*ouxgv8*_gcl_au*NTY2NTgwMjYuMTc0ODg4OTI3Nw..*_ga*MTU3ODM4MjUwOC4xNzQ4ODg5Mjc3*_ga_0YHJK3Y10M*czE3NTA0MjQyODUkbzczJGcxJHQxNzUwNDMwODk2JGo2MCRsMCRoMA.. )! messages.subject: Competition Launch: NeurIPS - Ariel Data Challenge 2025
messages.body:
Kaggle








Hi Nouman Usman,

Can ML models help uncover signs of life on distant worlds? That's what  
we're exploring in the NeurIPS - Ariel Data Challenge 2025.

In this competition, you'll work with simulated telescope data from the  
European Space Agency's upcoming Ariel mission to recover faint chemical  
signals from exoplanet atmospheres. These signals are incredibly subtle and  
often obscured by complex, time-dependent noise—making this a uniquely  
challenging opportunity for the Kaggle community.

You'll build models that clean up messy telescope data to detect the  
spectral fingerprints of alien atmospheres. The dataset includes realistic  
star–planet systems, stellar limb darkening effects, and a wide range of  
atmospheric profiles, helping scientists improve the accuracy of their  
analyses.





Total Prizes:

$50,000


Entry Deadline:

September 17, 2025




Learn More



Your work could help accelerate exoplanet research and contribute to  
answering one of astronomy's most profound questions: Are we alone in the  
universe?

Good luck,

Sohier Dane
Kaggle Data Scientist



Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043

This email was sent to noumanusman.uet@gmail.com because you indicated that  
you'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. If you don't want to  
receive these emails in the future, please unsubscribe here. You can also  
change your preferences on your account's profile page by logging in at  
kaggle.com.

messages.subject: Hackathon Launch: The Gemma 3n Impact Challenge
messages.body:
Kaggle








Hi Nouman Usman,

Can a compact, private AI model running right on your device make a real  
difference in the world? That's what we're asking in the Gemma 3n Impact  
Challenge.

In this hackathon, you'll use Gemma 3n, Google's latest on-device  
multimodal model, to build offline-first apps that address real-world  
challenges.

Whether that means helping students learn offline, aiding first responders

messages.subject: New Insights for Smarter Forms
messages.body:
Introducing Form Insights and more!

( https://tally.so/help/form-insights )

Hi Nouman ,

We’ve just launched Form Insights: your new superpower for understanding how people interact with your forms. From views to submissions and drop-offs, Insights help you spot what’s working (and what’s not) so you can make smarter tweaks, faster.
Discover Form Insights ( https://tally.so/help/form-insights )

( https://tally.so/help/form-insights )

The Tally API is now in public beta
-----------------------------------

Developers, rejoice! The Tally API ( https://developers.tally.so/ ) is officially out of private beta, ready for you to build integrations, automate workflows, and make Tally do more for you.

( https://developers.tally.so/ )

Form Version History is here
----------------------------

Made a change and want to go back? Now you can. Check out the new Form Version History ( https://tally.so/help/form-version-history ) to view and restore previous edits to your forms.

( https://tally.so/help/form-version-history )

Conditional logic update
------------------------

You asked, we built it! You can now use the new *"is not any of"* option in conditional logic. Perfect for excluding multiple answer options in one go.

( https://tally.so/help/conditional-form-logic )

How Delta uses Tally for in-app surveys
---------------------------------------

Learn how investment platform Delta strategically uses in-app surveys to capture user insights and guide product decisions throughout the customer journey. Read the story here ( https://tally.so/customers/delta ) (templates included!).

( https://tally.so/customers/delta )

Creator highlight
-----------------

Growth advisor and founder of Growthmates, Kate Syuma, created a powerful *User-centric Growth Surveys Pack* to help you build better products through feedback. It includes 3 ready-to-use Tally templates designed to uncover insights from onboarding, power users, and pricing feedback — so you can understand your users better and make smarter product decisions. Explore Kate’s Survey Pack ( https://katesyuma.notion.site/User-centric-Growth-Surveys-Pack-1adc390f366480d98bfbfc323ff49f06 ).

( https://katesyuma.notion.site/User-centric-Growth-Surveys-Pack-1adc390f366480d98bfbfc323ff49f06 )

A small favor, makes a big difference
-------------------------------------

As a bootstrapped company, Tally grows through word of mouth and the support of amazing customers like you. If you love using Tally, the best way to support us is by leaving a quick review. It only takes a minute, and it makes a huge difference. ❤️

Leave a review ( https://try.tally.so/g2 )

For a full list of updates, check out our changelog ( https://tally.so/changelog ) , and keep an eye on our roadmap ( https://tally.so/roadmap ) to see what's coming. We hope these new features improve your form-building experience, and we're excited to see what you'll create next.

Team Tally 🫡

Tally ( https://tally.so ) , the simplest way to create forms. Made and hosted in the EU 🇪🇺

messages.subject: 5 Days to Immortality! (Or at Least, World's Largest Hackathon Glory!) - World’s Largest Hackathon presented by Bolt
messages.body:
( http://devpost.com )

( https://worldslargesthackathon.devpost.com/ )

That's right, record-breakers: Just FIVE days remain to submit your masterpiece to the World's Largest Hackathon! June 30th at 2pm PT marks the deadline for history-making.

Haven't started yet?! On your marks, get set, GO! (We've got your back with our submission form video ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SylgkOajqrY ) if you need a walkthrough!) Double-check all teammates have joined—every name counts in the record books!

The Ultimate Submission checklist: 

* Are you creating a NEW application primarily built with Bolt.new?
* Have you added the Built with Bolt badge to the publicly deployed version (see guidance here ( https://worldslargesthackathon.devpost.com/details/badgeguidelines ))?
* Have you recorded a project demo video? Is your video uploaded to YouTube and public? Is it coherent and shows your app working? Remember that any content over three minutes will not be viewed by judges.
* Did you submit the project on Devpost here ( https://devpost.com/submit-to/24786-world-s-largest-hackathon-presented-by-bolt/manage/submissions?_gl=1*ouxgv8*_gcl_au*NTY2NTgwMjYuMTc0ODg4OTI3Nw..*_ga*MTU3ODM4MjUwOC4xNzQ4ODg5Mjc3*_ga_0YHJK3Y10M*czE3NTA0MjQyODUkbzczJGcxJHQxNzUwNDMwODk2JGo2MCRsMCRoMA.. )?  Your project should show as SUBMITTED and to be eligible it must include:
* A URL to a publicly available version of a project that meets all the requirements and is fully functional
* The Bolt.new project URL (must start with https://bolt.new/~/… ( https://bolt.new/~/%E2%80%A6 ))
* A text description that should explain the features and functionality of your Project and also explain how it meets any Challenge Requirements or Bonus prize.
* Selection of your geographical region and all Challenge and Bonus prizes and proof of eligibility to those. Only a few of the Challenges and Bonus prizes require something, but don't miss out on them:
* Make More Money Challenge requires a RevenueCat project ID.
* Voice AI Challenge requires an ElevenLabs account email address.
* Deploy Challenge requires a Netlify Team account's slug.
* Startup Challenge requires a Supabase Organization Slug.
* Blockchain Challenge requires a Algorand block explorer link to data related to project.
* Silly Sh!t Challenge requires a Reddit username and link to Reddit demo post.
* Custom Domain Challenge requires nothing extra!
* Conversational AI Video Challenge requires nothing extra!
* All of your teammates added as teammates. Remind them to accept the invitation so that they’re listed on the project!

 

Final Tip: Champion-level attention to detail! Scrutinize the Judging Criteria and Official Rules one last time. Even better? Get a second set of eyes on your submission, for that extra gold-medal edge.

This is your moment! Make it EPIC!!

 

You received this email because you signed up for World’s Largest Hackathon presented by Bolt. If you're no longer participating, you can unregister here ( https://worldslargesthackathon.devpost.com/ ).

messages.body:
FAQ: Confused about tracks vs. tech partners? Get the crystal-clear breakdown here & rock your hackathon project!

🔍 FAQ: EVERYTHING YOU NEED TO KNOW
ABOUT RAISE YOUR HACK !

RAISE your HACK ( https://lablab.ai/event/raise-your-hack?utm_medium=newsletter_paid&utm_source=emailFAQ9&utm_campaign=raise_hackahton )

Hey Innovator!
Are you ready to truly revolutionize AI? *RAISE your HACK* ( https://lablab.ai/event/raise-your-hack?utm_medium=newsletter_paid&utm_source=emailFAQ9&utm_campaign=raise_hackahton ) is here, so whether you're a seasoned pro or eager to dive in, this is your chance to build, innovate, and compete for a share of *up to $150,000 in prizes* , right from your couch or in iconic Paris!
As we've noticed some questions around the distinction between *Industry Tracks* and *Tech Partners* : consider this your essential guide to navigating RAISE your HACK and building something revolutionary.

*✅ HACKATHON REQUIREMENTS – READ CAREFULLY!*

*ALL PROJECTS (except for the Qubic Track -* *see Qubic's specific requirements on event page* ( https://lablab.ai/event/raise-your-hack?utm_medium=newsletter_paid&utm_source=emailFAQ9&utm_campaign=raise_hackahton ) *):*

* *MUST* integrate the *Groq API*
* *MUST* use at least *one Llama model (Meta)*

*🎯 INDUSTRY TRACKS = Your Main Focus & Core Challenge.*

These are the primary challenges you'll choose to tackle, defined by our leading partners. Your final project must address the use case from your *assigned track*.

*How to get assigned a Track (and officially participate!):*
1. *Register here:*

REGISTER NOW! ( https://lablab.ai/event/raise-your-hack?utm_medium=newsletter_paid&utm_source=emailFAQ9&utm_campaign=raise_hackahton )

2. *Create or join a team ASAP!* You cannot choose your track or officially participate without a team. This is a mandatory first step after registration.
3. Once your team is created, you'll receive a *Track Submission Form* via email, where you let us know your *top 3 Track preferences.*
4. Your team will then be *assigned to a specific Track* (you'll get an email confirmation once assigned).
5. *Crucially:* You need to change your Team Name to: *[Your Team Name - X Track]* (for instance: RAISEHackers - Qualcomm Track ). Only teams with a track name included will be considered for official participation.
*Our Current Industry Tracks* (All challenge details are listed on the event page!) *:*

* *Qualcomm Track*
* *Prosus Track*
* *Vultr Track*
* *Qubic Track*

*💡 TECH PARTNERS = Unlock Bonus Rewards & Supercharge Your Build!*

These partners provide cutting-edge technologies that you *can choose to integrate into your project within your assigned Industry Track* to qualify for *additional, special prizes!*
*Our Current Tech Partners:*

* *Groq* (mandatory for all Tracks besides Qubic)
* *Coral Protocol*
* *Fetch.ai*

GAME PLAN TO WIN BIG:

* *Stick to your assigned Track's Use Case:* This is your primary objective.
* *MUST USE:* Integrate *Groq* and at least one *Llama model (Meta)* into your project (if you're *NOT* on the Qubic Track).
* *OPTIONAL & REWARDING:* Use *Coral Protocol* and *Fetch.ai* within your assigned track to qualify for *extra prizes!*

*REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE:*
Let's say your team is assigned to the *Vultr Track:*
You *HAVE TO* stick to Vultr Challenge (described on the event page) & use *Groq* and at least one *Llama model (Meta)* in your project.
*BUT* you *CAN ALSO* implement *Coral Protocol* and/or *Fetch.ai* in your solution, and then you'll be in the running for not only the *Best Use of Vultr* prizes, but also *Best Use of Groq* , *Best Use of Coral Protocol* , and *Best Use of Fetch.ai* !

*NOW GET READY FOR RAISE your HACK!*

If you haven't registered yet, or haven't created a team: *do it now!* Don't miss out on the chance to win from our prize pool of up to $150k & code online or in Paris!

REGISTER NOW! ( https://lablab.ai/event/raise-your-hack?utm_medium=newsletter_paid&utm_source=emailFAQ9&utm_campaign=raise_hackahton )

Good luck!

messages.subject: ElevenLabs added to your BOLT BUILDER PACK - World’s Largest Hackathon
messages.body:
( http://devpost.com )

( https://worldslargesthackathon.devpost.com/ )

Thank you for joining the World’s Largest Hackathon presented by Bolt!

You previously received your builder pack, but were missing the ElevenLabs Creator Tier Access. Good news! We recently received more codes and are distributing to those that registered first.

IMPORTANT! You are responsible for any and all fees accrued in connection with this Contest. Be sure to monitor your usage as you are responsible for any and all fees accrued from use of any of the following developer tools if your use of these tools exceeds the provided access amount. Use of the developer tools will be subject to related license agreement.

 

NEW!! Creator Tier Access from ElevenLabs
-----------------------------------------

Get 3 months of ElevenLabs Creator Tier free which includes 100k credits/month, pro voice cloning, and 192 kbps audio. Go to https://elevenlabs.io/?coupon=WORLDSLARGESTHACK-170c4867

After signing up an ElevenLabs account (please choose developer category during sign up), click the above link to redeem the coupon code. After the code has been added to your account, navigate to the subscriptions section (My Workspace > Subscription), and select the Creator tier. The coupon will be automatically added on the checkout page. Please do remember to downgrade to a free account before the coupon runs out to avoid being charged. Thank you and happy hacking!.

The above should help you tackle the Voice AI Challenge! ( https://worldslargesthackathon.devpost.com/resources#voice-ai-challenge )
Refer to the docs for a quickstart ( https://elevenlabs.io/docs/conversational-ai/quickstart ) and detailed tutorial ( https://elevenlabs.io/docs/conversational-ai/guides/integrations/expo-react-native ). For support, join the ElevenLabs Discord Server! ( https://discord.com/invite/elevenlabs )

Please see all the rules and main requirements on the hackathon site ( https://worldslargesthackathon.devpost.com/ ).

If you run into any issues, please reach out to the support team of the specific tool above and don't hesitate to reach out on the Bolt Discord Server ( https://discord.com/invite/stackblitz ).

 

Here are the other items from your original Builder Pack
--------------------------------------------------------

 

Step One: Register for Free Bolt Pro
------------------------------------

Some of the other offers require you to have an active Bolt Pro account to work- which is free! Use this $30 code for a free Pro account or as credit when upgrading to a larger plan

$30 of Bolt.new credit: VGAKVG5Y
Go to Bolt’s pricing page ( https://bolt.new/?showPricing ) and click Upgrade to Pro. Use the provided promo code in the “Add promotion code” section. Provide a valid payment method and complete the checkout steps Already a paying customer? You’ll receive additional credit automatically when you apply the promo code.

 

Step Two: Redeem sponsor perks
------------------------------

RevenueCat is 100% free for Bolt participants, no coupon needed.
Our SDK helps you monetize your app in minutes, with support for mobile and web. You’ll only pay once your app’s making $2.5K+ per month. Build with Bolt, monetize and get paid with RevenueCat. Go to rev.cat/bolt ( http://rev.cat/bolt ) enter your email address and click Start for Free.

Free Domain for 1 year from Entri
Once you have Bolt Pro, claim your custom domain by visiting this page ( https://stackblitz.com/features/hackathon_2025/enable ). Sign in with the same credentials as your Bolt Pro account. Just build your app in Bolt, deploy it to Netlify, and then claim your free domain.

API Credit from Algorand/IPFS: BOLTdswvpdwrux512
Get 2 months of Nodely Unlimited API access (a $512 value) free. Go to nodely.io/bolt-new-promo ( https://nodely.io/bolt-new-promo ), click Redeem now, add your promo code at checkout, and complete with valid payment info to start your free trial.

2 Months Free Pro Access to Pica: GO-BOLT-9ae087d4
Get 2 months of Pro access, completely free — a $200 value. Enjoy all premium features with no restrictions. Available for a limited time. New users only. To redeem: Go to Pica Billing Settings ( https://app.picaos.com/settings/billing ) → Click Manage Plan → Select Pro → Enter your code at checkout.

6-Months of Monitoring with Sentry: bolt-sentry-wlh
Build with AI, debug with Sentry. Hackathon participants get 6 months of Sentry’s Team Plan for new organizations — includes error monitoring, logs, replays, and performance tracing. To redeem: Go toSentry Promo Page ( https://stackblitz.sentry.io/settings/subscription/redeem-code/ ) → Click Redeem Promo Code → Enter your code at checkout.

1 Free Month of Expo Production ($99 value) Code: Boltfriends
Build and ship unlimited during the hackathon with a free month of Expo's Production plan. To redeem: Create an account ( https://expo.dev/ ) → Go to Billing → View Plans → Select your account → Upgrade Plan → Enter the code at checkout.

$50 in Lingo credits: LINGODOTDEV049649
Localize your app in 85+ languages with $50 in credits (valid for 1 year after redemption). To redeem: Create an account ( https://lingo.dev/en ) → Go to Settings → Select Pro Subscription → Enter your code.

$25 in API Credits + 50% Off Dappier: BOLT50
Enhance your Bolt projects with AI search and custom copilots. Monetize with native ads or go ad-free with 50% off paid plans. All new users get $25 in free API credits. To redeem: Create an account → VisitSubscription Plan ( https://platform.dappier.com/subscription-plan ) → Select Starter Plan → Enter code at checkout.

50% discount for one year of 21st.dev ( https://21st.dev ): BOLT-YIHSR28H
Get full access to Magic AI and Pro tools for generating UI components. To redeem: Create an account → Go to Pricing ( https://21st.dev/pricing ) → Select Pro Plan → Enter your code at checkout.

Free 1-Year DEV++ Membership: X8PBRAYW
Unlock special DEV features and 20+ exclusive offers from top tech companies like Neon and .fun domains — great for experimenting and building. Go to https://dev.to/++, click Join DEV++ and follow the steps to enter your promo code and check out.

$150 in Free Tavus Credits
Get 250 free conversational video minutes, up to 3 concurrent CVI streams, and 3 free replica generations when you sign up or click this link ( https://dub.link/tavus-bolt-hack ) with an existing Tavus account. New limits are visible on your Tavus Portal billing page, with detailed usage under “invoice history.” Once credits run out, you can subscribe to a paid plan for more usage.

Host events & grow your following FREE on River, no coupon needed.
1. Build your following: host events in the Bolt community ( https://rvr.to/bolt ) (your attendees will automatically become your followers on River).
2. Host your own events: click “Create Event” and invite your followers.

3. Start monetizing: use your events to promote your paid product, host paid events, or get sponsors for your events on River.

For community builders looking to scale with global meetups, River is offering 50% off their Pro and Influencer Plans for 6 months. Reach out to the River team to set up a demo.

 

The above codes or URLs are unique to you and can only be used once. A maximum of ONE code per billing account can be applied for coupon codes from the same program.

Thank you,
Devpost + Bolt Teams

 

 

You received this email because you signed up for the World's Largest Hackathon presented by Bolt. If you are no longer participating, you can unregister here ( https://worldslargesthackathon.devpost.com/ ).

© 2025 Devpost, Inc. All rights reserved.

🥈 *2nd Place:* 💰 $3,000 USDT + Accelerated access to Qubic's Incubation Program

🤯 *FETCH.AI* ** ( https://fetch.ai/ ) *- New Tech Partner - Supercharge ANY Track!*
Your AI Agents are about to get a major upgrade! Say hello to *Fetch.ai,* now powering up RAISE your HACK as our newest *Tech Partner!* Their groundbreaking agentic AI stack is available for *ANY Industry Track* you tackle – Vultr, Prosus, Qualcomm, or Qubic... you name it!
Fetch.ai dares you to build agents that *THINK, reason, adapt, and interact in real-time.*

messages.subject: Drawing with LLMs: Our First Packages Competition Wraps Up
messages.body:
Kaggle








Hi Nouman Usman,

What happens when AI turns thoughts into pictures?

In our Drawing with LLMs competition, we asked participants to turn text  
prompts into SVG artwork using code-based models. It also marked the launch  
of Kaggle Packages, a new way to collaborate by sharing modular, reusable  
components like models, pipelines, and utilities.

All submissions were built as reusable packages, setting a new standard for  
sharing and scaling ML workflows on Kaggle.





Read More



The response included 1,742 participants across 1,313 teams, contributing  
nearly 39,000 submissions — all using Packages. Participants crafted  
creative SVGs, built robust pipelines, and explored new ways to turn words  
into visuals.

We're excited to share what's coming next — happy Kaggling!

The Kaggle Team



Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043

you'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. If you don't want to

messages.subject: Competition Launch: NeurIPS Open Polymer Prediction 2025
messages.body:
Kaggle








Hi Nouman Usman,

Polymers are everywhere, from the membranes for industrial separations to  
the plastic in your phone case. But discovering new sustainable polymers  
with specific properties is like searching for a needle in a haystack,  
especially without reliable data to guide the way.

In this challenge, you will develop machine learning algorithms to predict  
key polymer properties from a new dataset that is several times larger than  
any previous open resource, enabling faster and smarter virtual screening  
for sustainable materials.





Total Prizes:

$50,000


Entry Deadline:

September 8, 2025




Learn More



Your work could help redefine polymer discovery, accelerating eco-friendly  
innovation in everything from biomaterials to electronics.

Good luck,

Yao Yan
Kaggle Data Scientist



Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043

you'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. If you don't want to

messages.subject: Some code examples to explore Inngest
messages.body:
Hi again,

Most devs like diving into real code examples to learn how things work.

Here are a few of the most popular ones to get you started:

 * Framework project starters
   https://github.com/inngest/inngest-js/tree/main/examples - The fastest way to
   start building with Inngest in your favorite framework.
 * The Inngest demo app https://github.com/inngest/inngest-demo - A collection
   of different real life Inngest functions, including processing CSV file
   imports, scheduling monthly reports, and customer onboarding workflows.
 * Inngest + Resend for customer lifecycle emails
   https://github.com/joelhooks/inngest-resend-example - How to create
   Intercom-like email campaigns in just a few lines of code.

If you need anything, reply to this email. We are here to help.

Dan
Co-founder & CTO

messages.subject: [Product Update] New security enhancement for your Google Cloud environment
messages.body:
Re-authentication will be required for sensitive actions starting July 2025.




MY CONSOLE




Hello Nouman,

We're reaching out with an important update regarding enhancing the  
security of sensitive actions in your Google Cloud environment. This update  
strengthens protection against unauthorized access to your critical Google  
Cloud resources.

We have provided additional information below to guide you through this  
change.

What you need to know

Key changes

Starting in July 2025, to further protect your critical Google Cloud  
resources, you will need to re-enter your password or complete multi-factor  
authentication (MFA) for certain sensitive actions. These actions include  
billing assignment changes and IAM policy changes at the Organization,  
Folder, or Project level.

This additional authentication step ensures that only authorized users can  
make critical changes to billing and access control settings.

Re-authentication limitations

This re-authentication will initially apply to Google Cloud Console users  
with Google Cloud Identity. It will not apply to programmatic user account  
access or external identities federated through Workforce Identity pools  
and SSO.

Actions that require re-authentication

Specifically, you will be prompted to re-authenticate when performing the  
following actions (which correspond to these API calls):


resourcemanager.organizations.setIamPolicy
resourcemanager.folders.setIamPolicy
resourcemanager.projects.setIamPolicy
billing.accounts.setIamPolicy
billing.accounts.move
billing.accounts.removeFromOrganization
billing.resourceAssociations.create
billing.resourceAssociations.delete
resourcemanager.projects.deleteBillingAssignment
resourcemanager.projects.createBillingAssignment
resourcemanager.tagValueBindings.delete

Note: Service accounts are not affected by these new re-authentication  
requirements.

What you need to do

No action is required from you. This enhanced security will be  
automatically applied starting July 2025.

We're here to help

You can find more details about Reauthentication for Sensitive Actions in  
our User Guide. If you have any questions or require assistance, please  
contact reauth-for-sensitive-actions@google.com.

Thank you for your understanding and cooperation as we work to improve  
security in Google Cloud.

Thanks for choosing Google Cloud.





— The Google Cloud Team





DOCUMENTATION



SUPPORT




Was this information helpful?

Yes Neutral No


© 2025 Google LLC 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043

You've received this mandatory service announcement to update you about  
important changes to Google Cloud or your account.



Visit Google Cloud blog Visit GCP on GitHub Visit Google Cloud on LinkedIn  
Visit Google Cloud on Twitter

messages.subject: Inngest Changelog: May 2025
messages.body:
https://inngest.com

Hi Nouman,

May has been busy with numerous new features and developer previews 🚀


** Changelog
------------------------------------------------------------


** 🧪 Singleton functions: Prevent duplicate processing
------------------------------------------------------------

Singleton Functions is a new Flow Control feature available in developer preview that allows exclusive execution of an Inngest function.

Singleton Functions are useful when you want to ensure that only a single instance of a function is running at a time, for example:
* A third-party data synchronization workflow
* A compute- or time-intensive function that should not be run multiple times at the same time (ex: AI processing)

Learn more and see more examples on the documentation page (https://www.inngest.com/docs/guides/singleton?ref=newsletter-may-25)


** ↕️ Fetch APIs: HTTP requests made durable
------------------------------------------------------------

Now available in our TypeScript SDK, the new Fetch APIs (https://www.inngest.com/docs/features/inngest-functions/steps-workflows/fetch?ref=newsletter-may-25) enable you to offload slow requests to Inngest’s Infrastructure, making HTTP requests durable and reducing serverless execution costs.

Read the documentation (https://www.inngest.com/docs/features/inngest-functions/steps-workflows/fetch?ref=newsletter-may-25)


** 📊 Export metrics to Datadog, Grafana and more
------------------------------------------------------------

As more and more customers are growing with Inngest, we've seen a need to integrate Inngest metrics into existing monitoring and alerting systems. The Datadog (https://www.inngest.com/docs/platform/monitor/datadog-integration?ref=newsletter-may-25)  and Prometheus (https://www.inngest.com/docs/platform/monitor/prometheus-metrics-export-integration?ref=newsletter-may-25)  integrations are now available on all paid plans to export a wide range of metrics, from function runs, SDK requests, to step executions, into your existing monitoring and alerting systems.

Read the announcement blog post (https://www.inngest.com/blog/announcing-metrics-export?ref=newsletter-may-25)
Full Changelog (https://www.inngest.com/changelog?ref=newsletter-may-25)


** Week-end reads and tutorials
------------------------------------------------------------

The week-end is around the corner! Here are some resources to learn more or build projects with Inngest.


** Build an AI Podcast Clipping tool using Inngest and Next.js
------------------------------------------------------------

Feeling like building a project this weekend? 🛠️

Follow this YouTube tutorial to learn how to combine Inngest with modal and Next.js to build a complete AI Podcast Clipping tool.

Watch the tutorial (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=PeFZcvWucoU)


** Use Inngest to build Agentic AI workflows
------------------------------------------------------------

Tony, Inngest’s co-founder and CEO, recently gave a talk on Agentic workflows, covering how they different from RAG workflows and how Inngest’s DX is helping building them faster and in a reliable way ⚡

Watch the talk (https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tPjUgsE5PeQ)


** Community spotlight
------------------------------------------------------------

@pelaseyed (https://x.com/pelaseyed) created a OpenAI Codex clone in 2h using Inngest, VibeKit and E2B:
https://x.com/pelaseyed/status/1932516722373710039

More information and source code available on the X post (https://x.com/pelaseyed/status/1932516722373710039)

Thanks for reading! We're always looking for feedback, reply to this email or chat with us on Discord (https://www.inngest.com/discord) . Hope to chat with you soon!

Cheers,
The Inngest team

𝕏 (https://x.com/inngest) YouTube (https://www.youtube.com/@inngest) GitHub (https://github.com/inngest/) Discord (https://www.inngest.com/discord)

Copyright (C) 2025 Inngest

messages.subject: New Challenge - World’s Largest Hackathon presented by Bolt
messages.body:
( http://devpost.com )

Exciting news for participants! A brand new challenge has just been announced, offering another opportunity to win big and enhance your project.

Startup Challenge: Use Supabase to prep your Bolt.new project to scale to millions!

Supercharge your Bolt.new project with Supabase so you can scale to millions. If you need more than a database, Supabase provides auth, storage, and more. Submit your project by adding the organization slug to your app and show us you’re building the next big thing.

To kick this off, watch the previous virtual workshop on demystifying the backend. Watch here ( https://www.youtube.com/live/uIIHSCEwrgg?si=axbHJC9o5_iVwxK3 )

( https://www.youtube.com/live/uIIHSCEwrgg?si=axbHJC9o5_iVwxK3 )

Get ready to take your Bolt.new projects to the next level! We can't wait to see what you build. Good luck!

You received this email because you signed up for World’s Largest Hackathon presented by Bolt. If you're no longer participating, you can unregister here ( https://worldslargesthackathon.devpost.com/ ).

messages.subject: Welcome to Inngest 👋
messages.body:
Hi there,

Thanks for signing up for Inngest! Our goal is to help developers ship reliable
background logic without the headaches of local dev, infrastructure, and state
management. Whether you're building a simple background job, a complex workflow,
or distributed systems, we hope that Inngest can make your life easier.

This quick start tutorial
https://www.inngest.com/docs/quick-start?ref=email-welcome is the best way to
get up and running in less than 3 minutes. You can also read our docs
https://www.inngest.com/docs?ref=email-welcome for guides and examples.

Dan
Co-founder & CTO

PS - If you want to chat with a product expert about running Inngest at scale,
reply here or drop us a line https://www.inngest.com/contact?ref=email-welcome,
and we'll help with any questions.

messages.subject: Competition Launch: Make Data Count - Finding Data References
messages.body:
Kaggle








Hi Nouman Usman,

Scientific data power discovery and innovation - but they're often  
overlooked and rarely credited. Most research data go uncited, and even  
when referenced, it's hard to understand how they were used.

In this competition, your task is to identify and classify data citations  
in scientific literature as either primary (created for the study) or  
secondary (reused from elsewhere). Your work will help build a smarter  
model to automatically uncover and contextualize data use in papers.





Total Prizes:

$100,000


Entry Deadline:

September 2, 2025




Learn More



Your contributions will support Make Data Count's mission to recognize and  
reward data reuse, transforming how we value open scientific data in  
research.

Good luck,

Walter Reade
Kaggle Data Scientist



Kaggle, Inc 1600 Amphitheatre Pkwy Mountain View, CA 94043

This email was sent to noumanusman.uet@gmail.com because you indicated that  
you'd like to receive news and updates about Kaggle. If you don't want to  
receive these emails in the future, please unsubscribe here. You can also  
change your preferences on your account's profile page by logging in at  
kaggle.com.

messages.subject: Level Up Your Build with Claude Sonnet 4 + Week 2 Hackathon Updates
messages.body:
We’ve partnered with Anthropic to bring Claude Sonnet 4 to all Bolt users! Push your build to the next level.

Hey there,

We wanted to give you some Monday updates as we head into week 2 of the World’s Largest Hackathon! First, based on questions from participants, we’ve clarified some rules that will help you submit with more confidence. Watch the quick n’ easy video update here (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/VWD0b68HwpWVV96d5x1pFPwsW5DT7xy5xCjcKN31NNC23lcq-W7lCdLW6lZ3nbW97yxwt1xp2j6W5FC0ys3TJytsW8l0Svz5vRSxYVr7R7f4Z87bMVKmTdf5NB4FGVkth6Y5hzgC9W8B4_k47SfpBtVbdm5j1wl1fmW8TW5Hb1rzp_zW1nY4g819ttqJW2d_fXW3L99GcW4wVpxP5J3_QxW5786HR246ZlmW70f7d936h44_W3bjSM14jy0trW5j6tRJ1gyb69W4FFK3k81YsC7W3M00nG5gZt-qW8sBbsP5fcSHRW8F5T7V3Jcvd5N61tqSCf8c1GW3FP-gM4CL0flW43vQ-55h-JTJW8pQxd78FlDYldQfTy204 ) , or review the official rules (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/VWD0b68HwpWVV96d5x1pFPwsW5DT7xy5xCjcKN31NNC23lcq-W7lCdLW6lZ3q2N2FSNR5RgFN0W479X162MS5y1W44PFYj5pxpDxW6cb9nJ8GmxXrVl91gY2TkC9SV-Y3Lr4MJc_tW4dsQFV7V68FDW5PxX8-4G787SW8f5Fdb5F3YkLW2zfV2347PRC-W7zSCHX5rR4XYW1pP8VF5CWF9xW1hPJMk8qw7CcW5XgKNy6HpNVpW3FxsvN837NYdW8jBrcq1JQstdW96VQG47tr0N9W3sx2Yh2Y0n2rW6rNnf78tkBJpW501WTB75P9s6W3CTlbx4xDy9vW7hGyPc2YzLmfW5VWbmw1jkBGdV2nhLf1X10R9f8JKR9b04 ) for the full rundown.

It is not too late to register for the hackathon! Register (https://d5llC804.na1.hubspotlinks.com/Ctc/DQ+113/d5llC804/VWD0b68HwpWVV96d5x1pFPwsW5DT7xy5xCjcKN31NNBs3lcq-W69sMD-6lZ3nHW2YL0nN4T2Hj4W4wqDPC1LH0RHW8639dP1-sNzXW4BQPXs63NQ-3W4hnjvM2fhFmSW5Z-_Gq2MCwZ7W5czVNN2SRG3MVPXF7D6C3B8jW2GYnvP7JYflcW5cKmKq2shfVtVyV2Qk8BNd0TW1_fVf43SC9hJW94S_168W_ZD2W7M7LtF8vjyztW5KvZKL39x-sdVY_Xn04Z3WqKW4cLcRP1bzjcNW3Mq0Lt7D4T4_W2nKyH23q0MxGW7MT8l-17wy-hf2cv3xd04 ) for the hackathon to get your FREE Builder Pack which includes FREE Bolt Pro and much more. Existing Bolt subscribers may use the code for $30 off any subscription upgrades.The pack is sent to you via email within 48 hours of signing up, so be sure to sign-up asap!
